data.name: ExcursionExtranetWeb.MemberAdmin.Help.lblFAQ1
data.value: How do I setup my activity?

data.name: ExcursionExtranetWeb.MemberAdmin.Help.lblFAQ1Ans
data.value: A member user can set up his activity or excursion using Add/Edit Activity page. Here, the administrator can add information on the activity being setup. He needs to provide various details like Activity Name, Activity Type, Location, Activity Level, Activity Description, Inclusions, Terms and Conditionss etc. He has to select the days for which the activity will be available. Also, an image has to be uploaded for the activity being setup. User can setup the activity rate based on selection for Billing Type.

data.name: ExcursionExtranetWeb.MemberAdmin.Help.lblFAQ2
data.value: How do I configure rates and schedule?

data.name: ExcursionExtranetWeb.MemberAdmin.Help.lblFAQ2Ans
data.value: Member user can configure rates and schedule for the activity being setup. He selects billing type for the activity and add details in “Configure Rates And Schedule” page. For per person billing type, he has to provide information like per person price, date range, duration of the activity, different time slots, and maximum number of person allowed for booking in a slot. For Per Group type, he has to provide information like Per Group price, date range, duration of the activity, different time slots, and available quantity of Group for booking in a slot.

data.name: ExcursionExtranetWeb.MemberAdmin.Help.lblFAQ3
data.value: How do I stop sell an activity?

data.name: ExcursionExtranetWeb.MemberAdmin.Help.lblFAQ3Ans
data.value: A user can set stop sell for his activity from “Stop Sell” page. Here, the user selects the activity or excursion and set a date range as Black Out Dates. Black Out Dates are the dates for which the selected activity would not be available for online booking.

data.name: ExcursionExtranetWeb.MemberAdmin.Help.lblFAQ4Ans
data.value: User is allowed to upload multiple images from My Images page. For uploading an image, the user needs to select the Image category and Image sub category. Also, user has to specify image title and image description. Images uploaded in the system are displayed in a list. User can set any of the images as default. The user can delete any image but cannot delete the default image.

data.name: ExcursionExtranetWeb.MemberAdmin.Help.lblFAQ5
data.value: How can I publish tourist’s review?

data.name: ExcursionExtranetWeb.MemberAdmin.Help.lblFAQ5Ans
data.value: A tourist review can be published from Review Response page. Here user can select an Activity and view the feedback posted by all tourists about the activity. For a Tourist’s Response user can post reply for the feedback and click on publish control to get it publish on Booking site.

data.name: VehicleExtranetWeb.MemberAdmin.FAQ.lblAddOn
data.value:
What are the difference between AddOns and Facilities? Vehicle Extranet site offers various AddOns
and Facilities. Facilities are non-chargable features which has been associated while adding any vehicle in the
Extranet. While AddOns are chargable Facilities, while booking for the particular vehicle which has been setup at
the Extranet level. For example, While booking Limousine Champaign Shelf is non-chargable Facility and GPS
will be considered as AddOns.

data.name: VehicleExtranetWeb.MemberAdmin.FAQ.lblDateMsg
data.value:
In Vehicle Extranet we have kept the check, that no stop sell date range should beyond season
date range. At the time when user enters a specific date range which is not within a specific season, that comes
in the range of the Stop Sell Dates at that time 'Stop sell Date Range can not overlap the Season date range'
message will be displayed on the site.

data.name: VehicleExtranetWeb.MemberAdmin.FAQ.lblDuplicateDate
data.value:
All the policies are unique by Date range. None of the policy should be overlapped in a single date range. As an
when user will try to enter the same date which has been used in any of the previous policy creation at that time
'Duplicate Date range found. Please enter another value.' message will be displayed on the page.

data.name: VehicleExtranetWeb.MemberAdmin.FAQ.lblSippCode
data.value:
ACRISS is the Association of Car Rental Industry Systems Standards,The ACRISS codes are the vehicle
category codes and are established to help provide common standards for use when booking car rental
services through automated booking systems. These codes are also called Sipp Codes (Standard Interline
Passenger Procedure) as defined by the Acriss.

data.name: VehicleExtranetWeb.MemberAdmin.FAQ.lblStopSell
data.value:
Stop Sell is a kind of flag which sets to deactivate any particular entity associated with the Extranet
site. In Vehicle Extranet Site we offer Stop Sell on 4 different entities like Season, Location, Vehicle and
Vehicle Category. Stop Sell can be applied within specific date range or it can be permanent.
For Example if any Vehicle is having Stop Sell check than it wont be displayed in the Booking Engine.

data.name: ExtranetWeb.Common.multipleCancellationPolicyHelp
data.value:
Multiple cancellation policy can be setup from this page. Follow below steps to create multiple cancellation policy.

  1. Select cancellation policy period.
  2. Configure the charges for some number of days and save it.
  3. Verify configured charges in List charge criteria section.
  4. Click on save button in the Policy Detail section, if you do not want to configure policy for another criteria.
  5. If you want to define another cancellation criteria for same policy period, again configure the charges and click on save button in the Policy Detail section.
